{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"cruse-gnomonic-cowbird","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Why\n\nEpic 716f has drained the module-size allowlist to zero — every over-cap module is split and no `src/rebar/**/*.py` exceeds 800 LOC. Now retire the grandfathering ESCAPE HATCH so the 800 cap becomes absolute, and LOCK the limit so it cannot be changed through the normal contribution process (only an admin force-submitting past the gate can land a limit change). Per the operator decision, this is a CI-gate-in-code mechanism (no Gerrit ACL).\n\nThis is Phase 2a (the enforcement SWAP). It cannot also delete the allowlist/ceilings files, because the CI Module-size gate runs from MAIN's workflow against each change's tree — main's CURRENT (allowlist-based) gate would break reading the deleted `ceilings` file on this change's own CI. So 2a rewrites the gate + tests and ADDS the limit single-source, but KEEPS the now-empty allowlist/ceilings files; a follow-up (Phase 2b) deletes them once the new gate is live on main.\n\n## What\n\n1. Add `.github/module-size-limit.txt` containing just `800` — the SINGLE SOURCE of the limit, read by both the CI gate and the contract test.\n2. Rewrite the `Module-size gate` step in BOTH `.github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml` and `.github/workflows/test.yml` (keep the step NAME 'Module-size gate' so the parity test still finds it) to:\n   a. Read `LIMIT=$(cat .github/module-size-limit.txt)`.\n   b. ABSOLUTE cap: fail if ANY `src/rebar/**/*.py` (excluding `__pycache__`) has `wc -l` > $LIMIT. No allowlist, no exemptions.\n   c. LIMIT LOCK: `git fetch -q origin main`; `BASE=$(git show origin/main:.github/module-size-limit.txt 2>/dev/null || echo '')`; if `[ -n \"$BASE\" ] && [ \"$BASE\" != \"$LIMIT\" ]`, fail with an ::error:: saying the limit is LOCKED and an administrator must override the gate (force-submit) to change it. Also fail if the limit file is MISSING in the change (guards deletion of the lock). Bootstrap: on THIS change origin/main has no limit file yet, so $BASE is empty and the lock does not fire — it lands normally; every later change to the value trips the lock.\n   d. The step no longer reads `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt` or `.github/module-size-ceilings.txt`.\n3. Replace `tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py`: drop the allowlist/ceilings sync assertions; keep `compute_over_cap_modules`; read the cap from `.github/module-size-limit.txt`; assert (a) NO `src/rebar` file exceeds that cap, and (b) the limit file parses to a positive int.\n4. Update `tests/unit/test_ci_workflow_parity.py`: change the `_SHARED_GATE_SIGNATURES` entry `\"module-size ratchet\": \"module-size-ceilings.txt\"` to a signature the NEW gate contains in both workflows, e.g. `\"module-size gate\": \".github/module-size-limit.txt\"`.\n5. KEEP the (now-empty) `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt` and `.github/module-size-ceilings.txt` files in this change (Phase 2b deletes them). This keeps main's current gate green on THIS change's CI.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `.github/module-size-limit.txt` exists and contains `800` (verify: `test \"$(cat .github/module-size-limit.txt)\" = 800`)\n- [ ] The Module-size gate step in BOTH workflows reads the limit file and enforces an absolute cap with no allowlist read (verify: `grep -c 'module-size-limit.txt' .github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml .github/workflows/test.yml` is >=1 each, and `! grep -q 'module-size-allowlist' .github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml`)\n- [ ] The gate contains the limit-lock comparing origin/main's limit and failing on a change (verify: `grep -q 'must override' .github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml && grep -q 'must override' .github/workflows/test.yml`)\n- [ ] `tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py` asserts no src file over the file-sourced cap and passes (verify: `pytest tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py -q`)\n- [ ] `tests/unit/test_ci_workflow_parity.py` passes with the updated signature (verify: `pytest tests/unit/test_ci_workflow_parity.py -q`)\n- [ ] A locally-simulated limit change (edit the file to 900 and run the gate's lock check against a base of 800) fails with the override message; unchanged (800==800) passes (verify: run the lock snippet with BASE=800 LIMIT=900 -> exit 1; BASE=800 LIMIT=800 -> exit 0)\n\n## Notes\nPhase 2b (follow-up) deletes the orphaned allowlist/ceilings files, prunes the docs/architecture.md offenders table, and updates AGENTS.md — kept separate because the gate must stop reading those files (this change) BEFORE they can be deleted. E5: the gate is shell (oracle = running it against crafted trees, per the ACs); the contract + parity tests are the Python oracle.","id":"5f9d-ec9d-1cb5-4e82","parent_id":"716f-b917-9fc8-41f5","priority":1,"tags":["module-size"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Phase 2a: swap the module-size gate to an absolute cap + admin-locked limit"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784416775190656001,"uuid":"928b3417-bae5-4a6b-a7c4-198e3fe72d93"}